_library"}
{"title_page": "Royal Danish Library", "text_new": "{{Infobox library\n|native_name=Det Kgl. Bibliotek\n|native_name_lang =da\n|name=Royal Danish Library\n|image=Den Sorte Diamant 1.jpg\n|caption=The [[Royal Library, Denmark|Royal Library]] in Copenhagen\n|country=[[Denmark]]\n|location = [[Aahus]], Denmark,<br />[[Copenhagen]], Denmark\n|type=National Library, University Library, National Center for Shared Services for Public Libraries\n|established=1648\n|legal_deposit=Since 1697\n|collection_size   = 42,504,062 physical units,<br/>\n8,615,234<!-- 7,014,552+1,600,682 --> electronic titles (as of 2017)<ref name=Aarsberetning2017>{{cite web|title=\u00c5rsrapport 2017 for Det Kgl. Bibliotek | url=http://www5.kb.dk/export/sites/kb_dk/da/kb/aarsrapport/KB-Arsrapport-2017.pdf | date=5 March 2018 | publisher=Det Kgl. Bibliotek | accessdate=5 April 2020 | language=da }}</ref>\n|director=Svend Larsen\n|website={{url|www.kb.dk/en}}\n|num_employees=800+<ref>{{cite web|title=Job og karriere | url=https://www.kb.dk/om-os/job-og-karriere | publisher=Det Kgl. Bibliotek | accessdate=5 April 2020 | language=da }}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''Royal Danish Library''' ({{lang-da|Det Kgl. Bibliotek}}) is a merger of the two previous [[national libraries]] in [[Denmark]]: the [[State and University Library, Denmark|State and University Library]] in [[Aarhus]] and the [[Royal Library, Denmark|Royal Library]] in [[Copenhagen]]. Although now under a single organisation, the separate locations in both cities are maintained.\n\nThe merger came into effect on January 1, 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://kum.dk/nyheder-og-presse/pressemeddelelser/nyheder/det-nye-nationalbibliotek-kommer-til-at-hedde-det-kgl-bibliotek/1/1/|title=Det nye nationalbibliotek kommer til at hedde Det Kgl. Bibliotek|access-date=2018-03-03|language=da}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:National libraries]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox library\n|native_name=Det Kgl. Bibliotek\n|native_name_l